The paper deals with fairness in machine learning, specifically in the context of multi-armed bandit problems. This falls under the broad category of "machine learning" (cs.LG) and "artificial intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper also involves statistical analysis and confidence intervals, which could place it under "computational engineering, finance, and science" (cs.CE) and "data structures and algorithms" (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with information theory, specifically the KWIK learning model, which could place it under "information theory" (cs.IT).
